The paper discusses the development of autonomous agents that can interact effectively with other agents, which falls under the category of multi-agent systems. The paper specifically focuses on the ability of agents to reason about the behaviors of other agents, which is a key aspect of artificial intelligence. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Other likely sub-categories include cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), and cs.RO (Robotics), as these sub-categories are also relevant to the topic of autonomous agents and their interactions with other agents.
